'''贝塔斯曼基金会'''（{{lang-en|Bertelsmann Foundation}}，{{lang-de|Bertelsmann Stiftung}}）是德国最大的私人运营的[[非营利组织|非营利]][[基金会|基金会]]，<ref>[http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/cps/rde/xchg/SID-0A000F0A-CD13E0FF/bst_en/hs.xsl/2090.htm Foundation governance] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bertelsmann-stiftung.de/cps/rde/xchg/SID-0A000F0A-CD13E0FF/bst_en/hs.xsl/2090.htm |date=20140112173038 }} (from the official Bertelsmann Foundation website)</ref><ref>Mark Landler (October 8, 2002), [https://www.nytimes.com/2002/10/08/international/europe/08GERM.html Bertelsmann Offers Regret for Its Nazi-Era Conduct] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/10/08/international/europe/08GERM.html |date=20160603131446 }} ''[[纽约时报|New York Times]]''.</ref>1977年由{{tsl|en|Reinhard Mohn||Reinhard Mohn}}创立。截至2013年，贝塔斯曼基金会已持有德国[[跨國公司|跨国]][[大眾媒體|大眾媒體]]公司[[贝塔斯曼|贝塔斯曼]]的77.4%的股份。<ref>Chris Tryhorn (May 25, 2006), [https://www.theguardian.com/media/2006/may/25/citynews.business Bertelsmann agrees £3bn buyback deal] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2006/may/25/citynews.business |date=20171222142745 }} ''[[衛報|The Guardian]]''.</ref>

